      <bioghist id="aspace_2fa4dfa32d82c3c4362db4ecb0dc2b18">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Vladimir Sokolov-Samarin was a Russian émigré writer, anti-communist activist, and lecturer in Russian literature at Yale University from 1959 until 1976. In 1976, he resigned from Yale amidst controversery concerning his 1943 writings for <title render="italic">
               <part>Rech</part>
            </title>, a pro-Nazi Soviet newspaper.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_8b189ebe7d478678154c052ed05533ba">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of letters (some written in Russian), newspaper clippings, and articles documenting Vladimir Samarin's participation in pro-Nazi and anti-Semitic efforts in the Soviet Union, and Samarin's resignation from his post as a Yale Russian literature lecturer.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
